p A Website Strategy?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A <a href=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/digital-strategy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">website strategy<\/a> is a plan that helps businesses clarify the goals and KPIs for the new or redesigned website, as well as the path to reaching these.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As such it helps you:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Define your project and create a vision for your site structure and pages<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Determine your website\u2019s layout and core functionality<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Create a consistent design<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Develop strategic content that converts your prospects<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>And more<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Professional <a href=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/web-design-company\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">web design agencies<\/a> create these strategies for each project to deliver websites that attract the client&#8217;s target audiences and optimize conversions.<\/p>\n\n\n    <div class=\"cta-custom-box\">\n                    <span style='color: #008dde;'>Our experts build data-backed website strategies<\/span>\n                <a class=\"arrow-right black\" href=\"\/contact\/\"  rel=\"noopener\">\n            Set Up A Free Consultation        <\/a>\n    <\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"7-Key-Website-Elements-Every-Business-Should-Have\"><\/span>7 Key Website Elements Every Business Should Have<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are many components that make for a high-quality website. And with so many options out there, users can easily turn to a competitor if they are not satisfied with what they find.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are the top seven website elements that you should include to generate higher engagement and more conversions:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>1. Contact Page<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While its primary function is to allow visitors to get in touch with you, a contact page also tells them that you are a legitimate business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is especially important as there is a rising number of fake websites designed to trick users into providing sensitive personal details.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides building credibility and connecting you with prospects, contact forms help you collect the users\u2019 emails and use them for lead nurturing via email marketing campaigns (provided they opt-in, of course).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These are the contact details that you should include on your site:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Social media icons<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Business location<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Interactive map<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Phone number<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Email address<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fax<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Your contact page should be functional and responsive.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And to make it easily reachable and noticeable, ensure you place links both in the primary navigation and in the footer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2. Core Products Or Services<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Users visit your website for a reason. They are either interested in your content or in your products\/services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Highlight your offerings via dedicated pages or prominent sections within a one-page website.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on what you sell, include features, benefits, specifications and more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These are the pages that typically generate the highest number of leads as they are designed to solve your users\u2019 specific pain points or answer their requirements.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure that these pages are optimized for search engines to reach more highly qualified leads as they search the market for the solutions that you offer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>3. Headline &amp; Subheadline<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Your page headlines will tell your visitors what you are offering as well as highlight your unique value proposition.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Good headlines are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Specific<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Clear<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Accurate<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Keyword optimized<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Most visitors will only skim your web copy, relying on headlines and subheadlines to communicate the key points.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure that each page has one headline and several well-written subheadlines.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4. CTAs<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The purpose of CTAs is to make the visitors take a specific action that guides them through your website and moves them towards the bottom of the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/conversion-funnel-user-journey\">conversion funnel<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Each page of your website should have a clear purpose within the web ecosystem. As such, it features strategically created and placed CTAs to help users navigate the said ecosystem smoothly.<\/p>\n\n\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"How Blogging Benefits SEO\" width=\"798\" height=\"449\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/66NseuEURDU?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>5. Blog<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>As of May 2020, over <a href=\"https:\/\/www.worldometers.info\/blogs\/#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">4 million<\/a> blog posts are published every day on WordPress websites only &#8211; and for a good reason.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Blogging is an effective marketing tactic that:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Helps you rank for more targeted keywords<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Attracts more traffic via organic search<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Builds brand authority and credibility<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Helps move leads from awareness to the consideration stage<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>This is why 55% of marketers consider it as a top priority in their website content strategy. (HubSpot)<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>6. Success Indicators<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Success indicators like awards and industry recognition make brands more credible and desirable. These provoke curiosity among visitors as well as provide reassurance in the quality of the brand&#8217;s offering.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>The most common places to feature success indicator badges are:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Homepage (use sparingly)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Website footer<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>About page<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>7. Navigation Menu<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Invest time in your navigation menu. It will define your buyers\u2019 journey on-site, helping them understand the high-level website structure and how to navigate through it to find the information they need.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Complex or overly discreet navigation menus cause high bounce rates which, needless to say, means lost of lost business potential.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Focus on your target user behavior to design a menu that is intuitive as it is engaging.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>The most popular types of navigation menus are:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Interactive (\u201cregular\u201d header)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Double-tier (recommended for B2B and complex sites)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hamburger (recommended for brands with tech-savvy user base)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Static sidebar (mostly used by publishers)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:acf\/simple-cta {\"name\":\"acf\/simple-cta\",\"data\":{\"text\":\"Does your website have these key elements?\",\"_text\":\"field_636bafaacfde1\",\"color\":\"#008dde\",\"_color\":\"field_636bafbacfde2\",\"link\":{\"title\":\"Request A Website Audit\",\"url\":\"\/contact\/\",\"target\":\"\"},\"_link\":\"field_636bafe9cfde3\"},\"mode\":\"edit\",\"id\":\"block_acf-block-63af5c8cb243f\"} \/--><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading --><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What-Is-A-Website-Conversion-Funnel\"><\/span>What Is A Website Conversion Funnel?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Let\u2019s talk conversion first; A conversion refers to any predefined and desired action on your website, be it a successfully completed purchase, newsletter signup, a resource download, contact form submission or other.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>A website conversion funnel refers to the steps your leads take from the point at which they first land on your website to the point where they completed this desired action, i.e. convert.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>There are several stages prospects can go through:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Discovery<\/strong>: To make prospects aware of your existence create landing pages, ads, videos, infographics and other resources that will educate them.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Consideration<\/strong>: To make them engage, establish trust and reassure them that your product or service is a good fit for them, incorporate blog posts, case studies, reviews, emails, webinars and FAQ on your website.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Purchase<\/strong>: To influence their buying decisions and make them convert, leverage email and social media marketing to offer giveaways, coupons and more.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Why should you care about your website conversion funnel?<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>On the one hand, knowing at what stage of the conversion journey your prospects are, you can define the types of content to put in front of them.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>On the other hand, a funnel report can show you where you are losing your customers. It will tell you what you do right and what you do wrong as well as help you <a href=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/website-improvement\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">improve your website<\/a> selling strategy.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading --><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"10-Website-Strategies-To-Boost-Your-Online-Performance\"><\/span>10 Website Strategies To Boost Your Online Performance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Having a visually compelling website is one thing, but making it work and achieve your business goals is quite another.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>No matter your company size or industry, an effective website should achieve the following:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Attract qualified traffic<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Engage visitors<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Convert them<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Here are some proven website strategies that will boost your online performance and get your visitors to take action:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>1. Have A Clear And Compelling Value Proposition<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Your value proposition can determine the potential of your conversion rate to a great extent.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>It is the promise you give to make your products\/services attractive.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>A good value proposition solves problems and provides specific benefits your competitors can\u2019t cover.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>It is a unique identifier that tells your prospects why they should choose you over everyone else.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>This is why it should be authentic and different from the other websites in your industry.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>It should also be short, clear and easy to understand, as well as reflect your brand identity.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>2. Include Videos<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Research by HubSpot shows that 54% of consumers prefer to see video over any other type of content.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>In fact, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wyzowl.com\/video-marketing-statistics-2017\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">81%<\/a> of businesses say that their explainer videos have helped them generate higher sales.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>This is why video should be a part of your website strategy.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Selling is storytelling. And videos are the perfect way to share a story about your products, services or company.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>They keep your visitors engaged and make them stick around longer, which is great for better website performance.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>In fact, dwell time is one of Google\u2019s <a href=\"https:\/\/backlinko.com\/google-ranking-factors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">200<\/a> ranking factors.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>3. Improve Your Internal Linking Structure<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>A good internal linking structure should be part of your website strategies for two reasons:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>First, it is a great way to encourage users to engage and spend more time navigating your site. By using anchor texts in relevant and related content, you will increase interest in your readers.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Second, internal linking increases the number of page views, improves the time spent on site and boosts your search engine rankings.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>4. Add A Live Chat<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Research shows that the average time in which customer service representatives respond to client requests is <a href=\"https:\/\/www.superoffice.com\/blog\/response-times\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">12 hours and 10 minutes<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>However, 88% of them expect to receive a response within 60 minutes.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>If you fail to achieve this, you may lose a significant number of leads.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>The best way to improve customer support and satisfaction is to add a live chat to your website.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>With the rise of social media, web users are used to chatting so they prefer to talk with brands in real-time. This is why these forms are quickly becoming the leading customer service medium.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Live chats not only reduce support costs, but they also increase conversions and sales.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>5. Do A\/B Testing<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>According to a study by <a href=\"https:\/\/attachments.convertkitcdnm.com\/53948\/82211f69-0f8d-4c46-92f1-d7a968374773\/Copyblogger-How-to-Write-Magnetic-Headlines.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Coppyblogger<\/a>, 8 out of 10 users read headlines, but only 2 out of 10 read the body of your page.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>A good headline can make or break your engagement rates, and A\/B testing can help you identify the ones that work best.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>This process allows you to measure the performance of different headlines. You can test for headline length, tone and even usage of numbers.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>And this just one small, yet important element A\/B testing can help you improve.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>With this process, you can also enhance your:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>CTAs<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Images<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sales copy<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fill-in form<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>And more<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Incorporating A\/B testing in your B2C or B2B website strategies, you can improve content engagement, reduce bounce rates and increase your conversion rates.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>6. Offer A Lead Magnet<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Not all of your website visitors are ready to make a purchase and convert. Some of them are still at the top or in the middle of the conversion funnel.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>However, offering a lead magnet or free downloadable content (like an eBook or whitepaper) is a great way to build a relationship and trust.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>It helps you build authority, grow your email lists and attract people to engage.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>7. Use Call To Actions (CTAs)<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>We\u2019ve already covered CTAs earlier in this article, so let\u2019s take it a step further to identify the types of CTAs that perform the best.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>According to a study of 33,000 CTAs, HubSpot discovered that personalized calls to action convert <a href=\"https:\/\/blog.hubspot.com\/marketing\/personalized-calls-to-action-convert-better-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">202%<\/a> better.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>This is why you should focus on incorporating tailored CTAs, created with your content and audience in mind.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>8. Make It Responsive<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Last year, mobile devices were responsible for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.statista.com\/statistics\/277125\/share-of-website-traffic-coming-from-mobile-devices\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">52.6%<\/a> of the total website traffic.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>As smartphones and tablets are becoming the leading source of website visitors, responsive design is of key importance for user retention.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>This format enhances the users\u2019 browsing experience and increases search engine visibility.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>It contributes to faster pages, lower bounce rates and higher conversions.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>9. Incorporate Social Proof<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/bizrateinsights.com\/resources\/shopper-survey-report-the-impact-reviews-have-on-consumers-purchase-decisions\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">92%<\/a> of buyers read at least one review before making a purchase.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>The driving force behind <a href=\"https:\/\/medium.com\/@agencyworld\/got-ranked-by-a-rating-platform-like-designrush-the-manifest-heres-how-to-make-the-most-of-it-31fbd09ba29a\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">social proof<\/a> is the so-called bandwagon effect. It is a psychological concept which denotes that consumers are more likely to engage in action if others are doing it.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Social proof like case studies, testimonials and reviews ease the minds of the prospects, build trust and entice them to convert.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><\/p>\n<h3>10. Have A Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure (HTTPS)<\/h3>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Research shows every <a href=\"https:\/\/www.securitymagazine.com\/articles\/87787-hackers-attack-every-39-seconds\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">39 seconds<\/a> websites are threatened with a new hacker attack. And the best way to protect the integrity of your website is to invest in a Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure (HTTPS).<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>It will keep your communication, financial details and the privacy of your users\u2019 personal data safe.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>HTTPS protocol plays a huge role in boosting visitors\u2019 loyalty. It gives them peace of mind that they can trust your site. It decreases bounce rates and encourages users to engage and convert.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>What\u2019s more, this security extension also boosts your search engine performance since Google confirmed that it is one of the rankings signals.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":1276,\"className\":\"wp-image-1276 size-full\"} --><\/p>\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter wp-image-1276 size-full\">\n<figure id=\"attachment_1276\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1276\" style=\"width: 990px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-1276\" src=\"https:\/\/www.digitalsilk.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/wesbite-strategy-KPIs.jpg\" alt=\"web KPI measurement\" width=\"990\" height=\"660\"><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-1276\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Website traffic, bounce rate and top landing pages are some of the key metrics to help you measure your website strategies<\/figcaption><\/figure><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><!-- \/wp:image --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading --><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How-To-Measure-The-Effectiveness-Of-Your-Website-Strategy-Key-KPIs-To-Focus-On\"><\/span>How To Measure The Effectiveness Of Your Website Strategy: Key KPIs To Focus On<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) are measurable values that track the effectiveness of your website strategies.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>They demonstrate how successfully your brand is performing in relation to your business goals and objectives.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>These indicators provide you with useful information on your company&#8217;s progress and play a key role in decision making.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Since each website is different and has different goals, the KPIs that work for you may not work for another business.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>So, to define your KPIs and effectively measure your website strategies, you should determine your desired outcomes.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Make sure they are specific, measurable and relevant to your business.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Here are some of the most common metrics that can help you measure your website strategies:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Bounce rate<\/strong>: It refers to the percentage of single-page sessions in which users left without visiting another page. These are important to track since they can point to pages that load slow, irrelevant content and more.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Top landing pages<\/strong>: Looking at this metric, you can understand what are your best-performing pages that bring the highest traffic. It will also help you discover if your website content strategy works.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Conversion rate<\/strong>: It allows you to track the number of conversions and see how well your website is doing.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cart abandonment (eCommerce)<\/strong>: This metric will show you how many people place your products in their shopping carts and then leave the page without checking out.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>There are many tools that can help you track these metrics. However, looking at your Google Analytics is the most trustworthy source since the results come from the search engine itself.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:acf\/simple-cta {\"name\":\"acf\/simple-cta\",\"data\":{\"text\":\"Are you hitting your website KPIs?\",\"_text\":\"field_636bafaacfde1\",\"color\":\"#008dde\",\"_color\":\"field_636bafbacfde2\",\"link\":{\"title\":\"Consult Our Experts\",\"url\":\"\/contact\/\",\"target\":\"\"},\"_link\":\"field_636bafe9cfde3\"},\"mode\":\"edit\",\"id\":\"block_acf-block-63af5c8cb2469\"} \/--><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:heading --><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Takeaways-On-Website-Strategies\"><\/span>Takeaways On Website Strategies<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><!-- \/wp:heading --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>Your website is one of the most effective marketing tools.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>The key elements that you should include to achieve your business goals are:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Contact page<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Core products or services<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Headlines and subheadlines<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>CTAs<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Blog<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Success Indicators<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Navigation menu<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>For your prospects to convert successfully, develop the right content for each stage of the conversion funnel:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Landing pages, ads, videos and infographics for the discovery phase<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Blog posts, case studies, reviews, emails, webinars and FAQs for the consideration stage<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Giveaways, special offers and coupons for the purchase phase.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>To boost your online performance, focus on these website strategies:<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li>Have a clear and compelling value proposition<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Include videos<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Improve your internal linking structure<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Add a live chat<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Do A\/B testing<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Use CTAs<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Make your website mobile responsive<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Incorporate Social Proof<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Invest in HTTPS<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:list --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p>You can only achieve your objectives if you set the right KPIs. So, make sure they are specific, measurable and relevant to your business.<\/p>\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph --><\/p>\n<p><!-- wp:shortcode --><br><section class=\"form-section -wide -border colors-inverted\"><div class=\"form-section__wrap\"><div class=\"l-heading-v6\"><div class=\"c-heading -h2\"><div class=\"c-heading__pre\">Ready To Create A Market-Leading Website Strategy?<\/div><h2 class=\"c-heading__title\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Request-a-quote\"><\/span>Request a quote!<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2><\/div><\/div><div class=\"text-big\"><span>Tell us about your project and let our experts give you recommendations.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"l-form c-form\">\n<div class=\"wpcf7 no-js\" id=\"wpcf7-f349-o1\" lang=\"en-US\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<div class=\"screen-reader-response\"><p role=\"status\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-atomic=\"true\"><\/p> <ul><\/ul><\/div>\n<form action=\"\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/7584#wpcf7-f349-o1\" method=\"post\" class=\"wpcf7-form init\" aria-label=\"Contact form\" novalidate=\"novalidate\" data-status=\"init\">\n<div style=\"display: none;\">\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7\" value=\"349\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_version\" value=\"5.7.3\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_locale\" value=\"en_US\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_unit_tag\" value=\"wpcf7-f349-o1\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_container_post\" value=\"0\" \/>\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"_wpcf7_posted_data_hash\" value=\"\" \/>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"c-form__row\">\n    <div class=\"c-form__item -has-icon\">\n        <span 